      <h1 class="pb-5">How to Use</h1>
      <h4 class="pb-3">Follow the procedure below :</h4>
      <p>1. Select your trip type. (Tour , Goods Transportation , Roadtrip , Walking Trip , Passenger Buses)</p>
      <br>2. Customize your trip type by clicking on tour button and selecting Type of trip , mode of travel, and optimizatioon options .  <br>  <b>Remember, you should either select a trip type option or click on the
          custom trip button. If you do both, the output will be based on the latter.</b></br>
      <p>3. Enter planned number of cities and press SUBMIT button without hesitation .</b></p>
      <p>4. If you missed a step from above before clicking the submit button, you'll receive an error. Read the error
        message carefully and follow the instructions provided.</p>
      <p>5. If it's submitted without any errors, you can proceed.</p>
      <p>6. First, enter your starting city in the provided box.</p>
      <p>7. You will receive suggestions after typing at least 3 letters. It's recommended to select values from the
        suggestions to prevent errors due to spelling mistakes.</p>
      <p>8. Once you press Enter after inputting the starting city name, a notification will appear on the screen
        indicating you can enter the names of the remaining cities in any order.</p>
      <p>9. If you've chosen different starting and ending locations, you'll need to enter the ending location
        immediately after the starting one. You'll be notified of this after submitting the starting location.</p>
      <p>10. Once you've entered the names of all cities, the submit button will be hidden. Wait a few seconds, and your
        route will be displayed.</p>
      <p>11. Scroll down to view your route. If you'd like to try a different route, click on the reset button to start
        over.</p>

      <h4 class="pb-3 pt-5">Specifications of Mentioned Trips:</h4>
      <p>1. <b>Tour</b>: Type of trip - <i>Round trip</i>, Mode - <i>Drive</i>, Optimized by - <i>Time</i>.</p>
      <p>2. <b>Goods Transportation</b>: Type of trip - <i>Different starting and ending locations</i>, Mode -
        <i>Trip</i>, Optimized by - <i>Distance</i>.</p>
      <p>3. <b>Roadtrip</b>: Type of trip - <i>Round trip</i>, Mode - <i>Drive</i>, Optimized by - <i>Distance</i>.</p>
      <p>4. <b>Walking Trip</b>: Type of trip - <i>Round trip</i>, Mode - <i>Walk</i>, Optimized by - <i>Distance</i>.
      </p>
      <p>5. <b>Passenger Buses</b>: Type of trip - <i>Different starting and ending locations</i>, Mode - <i>Drive</i>,
        Optimized by - <i>Distance</i>.</p>
